characteristics of your usage, not a breakdown\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B61% of your usage hit a >100k-token cache miss\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mUncached\u001b[14Ginput\u001b[20Gis\u001b[23Gexpens\u001b[30Gve, and\u001b[39Gf\u001b[41Gen happens when sending a message to a \r\u001b[4C\u001b[1Bsession that has gone idle. /compact before stepping away keeps the cold-start \r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;153;153;153msmall.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B22% of your usage was at >150k context\r\u001b[4C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mLonger sessions are more expensive even when cached. /compact mid-task, /clear \r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mwhen switching to new tasks.\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B46% of your usage came from MCP server\u001b[43G\"plugin:total-recall:total-recall\"\r\u001b[4C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mMCP tool results stay in context for the rest of the session. /compact to flush\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;153;153;153mthem, or disable servers you don't need.\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1BSkills\u001b[28G\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m% of usage\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B/\u001b[6Glaude-api\u001b[39m             \u001b[36G\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m7%\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B/total-recall:memory-workfl…\u001b[36G5%\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B/sup\u001b[9Grpowers:systematic-deb…\u001b[36G5%\r\u001b[3C\u001b[2B\u001b[39mPlugins      \u001b[28G\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m% of usage\u001b[39m\u001b[45;1H\u001b[4;32H\u001b[?2026l"]
