[171.945553, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[3C\u001b[36B\u001b[38;2;177;185;249ms3             \u001b[64Gaws-dev-too\u001b[76Gkit) Deep-dive in\u001b[96GAmazon S3 bucket configuration,\u001b[128Gstorage optimization, and access c\u001b[163Gntrol. Use when designing\r\u001b[62C\u001b[1BS3 storage \u001b[75Gtrategies, conf\u001b[91Ggu\u001b[94Ging bucket\u001b[105Gpolicies\u001b[114Gand access co\u001b[129Grols, op\u001b[138Gimizing\u001b[146Gperformance for larg\u001b[167G-scale workloads, set\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bs\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mcan       \u001b[63G(aikido) Run\u001b[38;2;177;185;249ms\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m an Aik\u001b[84Gdo\u001b[87Gsecurity scan on generated, added, or modified code files to detect SAST\u001b[160Gvulnerabili\u001b[172Gies and exposed\r\u001b[62C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;177;185;249ms\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mecrets. Use\u001b[76Gwhen the user wants to\u001b[99Gscan code\u001b[109Gfor security issues, after writing or modifying code, or when \u001b[172Ghey\u001b[176Gm\u001b[178Gntion A\u001b[186Gki\u001b[39m\u001b[45;1H\u001b[42;5H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
